{
  "stem": "18932.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 37.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "These were the, the Jewish policemen, the Jewish kapo-- the, the Jewish policemen in the ghetto, yeah.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, no, not the kapo, not yet, not in the ghetto, no.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were not kapos.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were just policemen, yeah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there was a lot of hunger.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was a lot of people who were very hungry.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember my cousin came to the house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't remember her name-- or was it acquaintance?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she was all swollen from hunger.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was just impossible.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People were eating anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They made pancakes from grinds of coffee, grinds from beets, leaves, anything they could.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was really very bad.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "People were really starving and hungry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Whatever little we had they cooked.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother used to cook.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was too young to--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was a stove and--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So going back to the family that we lived with--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were very mean to us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because when my mother-- when-- after they finished their cooking, they would put water on the-- on the fire.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother had to start it from scratch.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was really very bad.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after a few more times when they came-- and the next time, my mother gave them some rice, which my father was-- my uncle from America-- my uncle left to America in 1939.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he sent us two packages to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And because my father worked at-- there, he was able to get those packages.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And in one was some cocoa, some rice, even some butter, which was fresh.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And really, this, this-- my mother used it so sparingly, that we had it for a long time.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So once she gave them some rice, and they left again.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
